{
  "text": "where, Vk is the vol% of the KF, Ds is the density of the K FRC sample, Dr is the density of resin matrix and Df is the density of the KF (1.44 g/cm [CITATION_1] ). This method determines the densities (calculated by Archimedes' principle) of FRC sample and resin composite matrix samples by measuring their mass in air and water. An analytical balance (AG 204, Mettler Toledo, Greifensee, Switzerland) equipped with a density kit was used for the measurements.",
